Celebrated Bongo rapper AY, real name Ambwene Allen Yessayah, on Saturday said 'I do' to his long time Rwandese fiancée Remy at a colouful ceremony in Kigali. The two are said to have have been dating since 2008 although the rapper only revealed his fiancée identity sometime in 2016. The private wedding which was held at Golden Tulip Hotel in Rwanda and was attended by who is who in the entertainment industry across East Africa. Radio personality Shaffie Weru, former entertainment journalist John Muchiri and fashion designer Fundi Frank are among the Kenyans who were on the guest list. AY began his career with the group S.O.G. before going solo in 2002. He has also collaborated with Nyashinski.